[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man, 79, dies after being hit by lorry in Buxton

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 79-year-old man has died after being hit by a lorry.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The man was killed in the incident in Fairfield Road, near to the junction of Lightwood Road, in Buxton at 17:45 GMT on Thursday.
Derbyshire Police said a 40-year-old man has been arrested on suspicion of causing death by careless or inconsiderate driving.
Officers said the man was due to be interviewed later on Friday.
